{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Change the law so that marriage does not revoke a will",
        "additional_details": "There are experiences where parents remarry, in some cases overseas, new spouse and their family to comes to live in the UK, when the parent of first families dies, the first family possessions, their parent's pensions, savings, everything goes because the Law discards wills if the document pre dates a marriage, even if the deceased had the time to include or hand over to new spouse.",
        "background": "Either amendment to current Law, or Bill to legitimatize wills or establish a mechanism that would consider each situation. Currently we believe the law is prejudice against first families who have built and acquired all the family assets and second marriage means everything goes to them.",
